    public class DuplicatedMathValidationFunction<T extends MathContainer>
extends java.lang.Object
implements ValidationFunction<T>
    Class used to check if the 'math' mathML element is duplicated.

    In some cases, check as well if at least one 'math' element is present

    Author:
    rodrigue

      • DuplicatedMathValidationFunction

        public DuplicatedMathValidationFunction​(boolean mathIsRequired)
        Creates a new DuplicatedElementValidationFunction instance.
        Parameters:
        mathIsRequired - boolean to indicates if the math is required of not. It allows to differentiate rules that tell "must have one and only one math element", from rules that tell "may have one and only one math element". Or make the math required for some elements for SBML Level 3 if required.
